summary: An Ordinance appropriating from the general fund the sum of Forty ($40.00) Dollars, and authorizing and directing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue and sign a warrant in said sum against said fund, payable to the clerk of the Superior Court, in an for King County, and authorizing and directing the City Treasurer to pay the same, and repealing Ordinance No. 22773 entitled "An Ordinance authorizing and directing the mayor and City Comptroller to issue and sign a warrant in the sum of Forty ($40.00) Dollars, payable to Clerk of the Superior Court, in and for King County, and authorizing and directing the City Treasurer to pay the same" approved December 16, 1909.
